‚ú®on ‚Äúspin days‚Äù (currently Monday, Wednesday and Friday) users wait for a notification and jump into the app to cop the featured collectible and earn free tickets to spin the neon flywheel, where they can win variable token rewards from a $1500 prize pool (sometimes $BETR, sometimes tokens from partner projects looking for distribution)

People seem to like all this, because 31B tokens have been staked already representing 55% of circulating supply üí™ 

‚ú®We hired @burr.eth a couple months back as our CFO (Chief Fun Officer) and she does an awesome job running community initiatives like regular freeroll poker games, art contests and more. 

‚ú® Our favorite thing about building on @base.base.eth and Farcaster is the composability of the tech + the collaborative nature of the builders here, so we love jamming with other projects and communities to cross-pollinate and grow the pie.

text:
Security Update üö®

Recently, attackers gained access to a personal device and compromised certain Degen hot wallets previously used for smart contract deployments.

Here is everything you need to know üëá

Before major harm could occur, we secured and transferred ownership of all deployed contracts, including the Degen airdrop, LayerZero contracts, and other critical deployments.

Unfortunately, the attackers were able to steal roughly $300k worth of locked AERO and $200k from our Solana Degen pool.

WHAT‚ÄôS SECURE

Our treasury (the most critical piece),
All deployment wallets (migrated to new infrastructure),
and our social accounts.

STEPS WE‚ÄôVE TAKEN

Since then, we‚Äôve moved all operational funds and deployments to hardware wallets, brought in top security experts to reinforce every layer, and tightened protections across devices, emails, and infrastructure.

COMMUNITY IMPACT

For the community, nothing changes.

Degens can continue using products as usual. Your holdings are safe, and the ecosystem remains intact.

One important note: any posts, emails, or messages that appeared between 6pm and 8pm (Poland time) yesterday did not originate from our team. We want to be clear that communications during that window should not be trusted.

Please stay extra cautious of phishing and fake accounts in the coming days.

This is a tough moment, but far from the end of the world.

We‚Äôre committed to learning from this, closing every gap, and continuing to build a stronger, more secure future for the Degen community.

The hat stays on. üé©

If you see this post! MUST RECAST 

Don‚Äôt not interact with such tokens or your Farcaster wallet will forever be on Draining mode. 

This is my wallet. Coin has no history or whatever.

‚ú® FAQ: So You Got A Weird Token In Your Warpcast Wallet ‚ú® 

Warpcast Wallet hides spammy tokens by default, but you may notice unknown tokens listed if you choose to tap "Show All." These are almost always spam or scams. And once in a while a spammy token makes it past the filter. These tokens will usually try to trick you into visiting a malicious website by displaying a link in the token name or in an error message.

The best and safest thing you can do is to IGNORE THEM. Just don't interact at all.

Q: I got an unknown token. What should I do with it?
A: Ignore it.

Q: It says it's an airdrop. Is this free money?
A: No, ignore it. This is a scam.

Q: Should I send it out of my wallet?
A: No, ignore it.

Q: Should I swap it for another token?
A: No, ignore it.

Q: There's a website in the token name, should I visit it?
A: No, ignore it. The link is a scam.

Q: I tried to swap it and the error says to go to a website. Should I visit it?
A: No, ignore it. The link is a scam.

If you're teaching people about tokenomics, then it's equally important to understand how to hedge against risks before engaging, and what tools you have at your disposal to help out.

If you're new to this space you're probably not going to know what to look for to avoid being rugged, but having LLMs at your disposal radically changes that.

One of my favourite use cases for @askgina.eth is to do a token analysis so I know what red flags I need to navigate. What I like about Gina is that it presents this in a digestible way, and how simple prompts go a long way to better understand how to properly navigate all this.

(I've already given them .005 eth each plus some usdc to use during the class for various assignments).

I'll also be incorporating this token into Noice for tipping of students who interact on Farcaster. Just giving everyone a heads up on the plans for this token.

text:
Okay - Take 2‚Ä¶ Clanker v4 liquidity‚Ä¶ as I casted literally into the void this AM.  Decided to rewrite since thought more folks would benefit from understanding pool mechanics.  Hope Dish will correct me if I‚Äôm incorrect.

The way the lp is set up for $likes is there are 5 pools which ‚Äúunlock‚Äù as the market cap rises

10% at launch
50% at 130K
15% at 450K
20% at 50M
5% at 500M

Two notes >

This will tend to push tokens that are solid to the 450K range pretty quick, as the available liquidity starts ‚Äúshallow‚Äù

Once above 450K MC the liquidity shown on dex or gecko includes 25% still salted away.

So for $likes the active lp is
currently 8.63B Likes $225K and 309K WETH.

This functionally overstates the available liquidity at a glance; yet shows the depth that will get added when a token really cranks - say if a token matched $BNKR or $CLANKER s run.

Think this is a great strategy long term for encouraging sized trades on dex for the most successful tokens as liquidity will be thick when tokens reach 50M & 500M

There is also a variable fee function that increases the swap fee during times of greatest volatility, capturing fees for the token launcher.

Also should be noted if a team that clanks sets aside a percentage of the supply at launch or competes a dev buy these would further reduce circulating supply.  Would love a way for these situations to be easily noted looking at a token.
